      <bioghist id="aspace_02efc7090ad7b55439c3a3a365bee3ae">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>Milton Bulkley was born on July 14, 1840, in Southport Connecticut. He graduated from Yale in 1861. Due to declining health after graduation, he was advised to take a sea voyage. In late 1862 he travelled by sea from New York to San Francisco. California suited him, and he remained there as a member of the firm, Sherwood, Bulkley &amp; Company, shipping and commission merchants. His health began to decline again in 1866. In 1868 he married Kate A. Wheaton. They had one son. He died in San Francisco on January 25, 1872.</p>  
      </bioghist>
      <arrangement id="aspace_0836be681ce7bbe8cd3a48653ff66731">
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <p>Arranged alphabetically by type of material.</p>  
      </arrangement>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_a03c2e7e0d913b88f5e8b8c17b615580">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The papers consist of a journal/log Milton Bulkley kept on his 1862 sea voyage, a typed transcript of the log, a Yale class book of 1861, and a Yale College catalogue, 1857.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
